# `test/` — skill tests & fixtures

All **automated tests** for this skill live under **`test/`** (not at repo root).

| Subfolder | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **`fixture/`** | Optional **frozen inputs / snapshots** (e.g. `fixture/<scenario>/`) used by tests or docs. |
| **`<workspace>/`** | Optional **active workspaces** for `conf/abd-config.json` **`active_skill_workspace`** (paths relative to skill root), e.g. **`test/mm3`**. |

- Tests should exercise **`scripts/`** (and scanners) the same way operators run them.
- Keep **fixtures** small and intentional; document what each scenario proves.
- If you use **pytest**: add **`pytest`** to **`requirements-dev.txt`** (or dev extras), document **`python -m pytest test/`**, and read **`abd-skill-builder`** **`content/parts/library/skill-repo-standards.md`** → *When automated tests are asked for* — **operator** does not run pytest by default.

See **`abd-skill-builder`** **`content/parts/library/skill-repo-standards.md`** — **Tests & fixtures** row.
